			<h2>12th Sandstone, 255, Mid-Autumn</h2>
			<p>So there must be another vampire on the loose in the fortress. Hunting vampires wasn't on the job application nor was it on my resume, so I'll leave that to someone else. I'm starting to rethink my current role as Overseer, here. Many dwarves are upset their children being missing. I put an amber alert out on some stone slabs but I guess that wasn't enough.</p>
			<p align="center"><a href="images/suc_img/year5_25.png"><img class="bigcenter" src="images/suc_img/year5_25.png" /></a></p>
			<h2>17th of Sandstone, 255, Mid-Autumn</h2>
			<p>Sad news from back home as my son, Dastot, arrived unexpectedly. My wife and his mother, Bembul, was mauled by a wolverine last month. The doctors sent me the diagnostic and it was straight to the point:</p>
			<p align="center"><a href="images/suc_img/year5_26.png"><img class="bigcenter" src="images/suc_img/year5_26.png" /></a>
			<p>Yet she still lives! So bless the Gods, I suppose. It makes me think twice about the tame one we keep outside. I have no urge to travel home now, the sight of her may ruin the way she'd want me to remember her by. I'm finding the Dining Hall to be the only thing I look forward to working on each day. In her name I will call it the <strong>Bembul Grand Hall</strong>. I also wish to be buried within its walls, so I ordered my son to begin work on a tomb immediately. Winter is coming.</p>
